text: Mill Run is a tributary to Neshannock Creek in western Pennsylvania. The stream rises in southeastern Mercer County and flows generally northwest entering Neshannock Creek near Milburn, Pennsylvania. Mill Run watershed is roughly 36% agricultural, 56% forested and the rest is other uses. ==References== Category:Rivers of Pennsylvania Category:Tributaries of the Beaver River Category:Rivers of Mercer County, Pennsylvania
